byline.original: By MICHAEL J. DE LA MERCED and EVELYN M. RUSLI

abstract: The company is considering raising its I.P.O. price above the current expected $16 to $18 a share on heightened investor demand, according to people briefed on the matter.
snippet: The company is considering raising its I.P.O. price above the current expected $16 to $18 a share on heightened investor demand, according to people briefed on the matter.
lead_paragraph: It appears investors are flocking to Groupon's forthcoming initial public offering like customers to one of the daily deal giant's coupons.
